data.content:
Yes! Use **ValueTuples** instead of `object[]` for type safety (MSTest 3.7+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string input, bool expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Benefits:**
- **Type safety** — no boxing, no runtime casts from `object`
- **Named parameters** — self-documenting test data
- **Compile-time errors** if you pass the wrong type

The test method signature stays the same; MSTest destructures the tuple automatically.
